      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of July 9 What Doing column about Philadelphia which misstated $20 fare for ride downtown from airport (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A report in the Travel Advisory column on July 9 about the reopening of the Savoy Hotel in Florence referred incorrectly to the first occupant of the building. The banker for whom it was built in 1893 was Italian; a news release referred to him as an Israelite because he was Jewish, but Israeli nationality has existed only since 1948.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
